You do a very nice job of explaining the ideas you choose to emphasize. You create a nice scenario. One idea to consider:
Pressley's ideas about learning strategies may relate to social behaviors. One of the things that needs to be done in teaching
strategies, is to make the strategy overst so that it can be observed and modeled. One of the things that socially deficit
children may need is modelling of what are normally covert processes. How does a good social skill person decide what to
do? It probably has become automatized in you, but what kinds of thinking might you have to have had to go through.
Perhaps these thinking processes need to be modelled. 
